<h3>We suggest the following:</h3>

<ol>
  <li>
    <h5>Scaffolding engine</h5>
    <p>Open your shell in the root of your microscope project and type the following command : 
      </br><pre class="accentbg" style="color:white; padding:8px;">node microscope.js generate_crud [entitiename] [nameofproperty1]:[string] [nameofproperty2]:[text] ....</pre>(without [])
    </p>
    <p>microscope scaffolding engine allow you to create controller, api, services, model and views quickly for rapid development.</p>
  </li>
  
  <li>
    <h5>Try this out on a mobile device</h5>
    <p>microscope framework supports various template options for viewing on mobile devices as recommend in Node.js Webmatrix samples.</p>
  </li>
  
  <li>
    <h5>The power of JavaScript</h5>
    <p>microscope framework come with a large choice of JavaScript librairies. Mobile views (jQueryMobile), DOM/Ajax manipulation (jQuery), client-side MVVM pattern (Knockout), notifications (toastr).</p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <h5>Authentication</h5>
    <p>microscope framework use <b>passport.js</b> to perform user authentication with locals or with oAuth data.</p>
  </li>
</ol>

